verbs.description: unnotify (third-person singular simple present unnotifies, present participle unnotifying, simple past and past participle unnotified)

examples: I notified to you the settlement of the Ministry, and, contrary to late custom, have not to unnotify it again. However, it took ten days to complete, after an inter-ministerium of exactly three months.

entries.meaning: (transitive, rare) To notify (a person) that a prior notification should now be disregarded.
examples: "Well, you unnotify the railroad," Mugivan stormed.
